While Brain Uploading (as tvtropes calls it) isn't an uncommon trope, most of the stories about it seem to focus on the philosophical questions that come with it. I haven't seen much that covers what it would actually be like for the AI, aside from handwaving it with a physics simulation or the like. What would it look like when you take a copy of someone and then drop it into a computer?

This is a story about that.

Thanks to Doctor Fullham for crit!

Also, credit goes to these people who were crazy enough to let me use their characters:

MoreWorldliness
detectiveroscoe
Calibri Bold
TheManhattenProject


EDIT 2021/1/2:  I went with the current version of the text logs as a stylistic choice, but I realized later that it might be nice for translators or whoever to know who is talking. So here's a color-coded version!





